☕️ Children’s Sustainable Coats ☕️ 
-
Here’s the tea: it’s an investment. We offer a sustainably/ethically sourced selection with high function and elegant fashion, making these pieces worth the price tag for multiple years of wear. You’ll want to buy the next size up for 2-3 years of wear per child, and the incredible quality of these coats means they can be worn by multiple children over many years. 
-
The majority of coats on the market are made of petroleum based synthetic fibers & the high performances coatings mostly utilize harmful chemicals. 
-
Our water repellent coats have bionic finish which is an ecological performance solution, they are also made of ♻️ materials. The boiled wool coat is one of the warmest naturally functioning materials. It naturally repels water and does not get cold when wet.
-
The collection is not completely zero waste, it’s not 💯 sustainable, but it’s a hefty foot in the right direction with what’s currently available on the market. With your purchase, we can move the industry forward. 🧥 ♻️ 😇

Do you think sustainable outerwear is worth the investment? Tell us your thoughts in the comments! 👇🏼

We took a minute to tally figures from 2022. Here’s what we found: 👇🏼

We carried
🌟 74 brands with verified ethical labor practices
🌟 34 brands that utilize verified sustainable materials
🌟 30 brands with local USA made manufacturing 
🌟 (and because we are about diversifying, and are ourselves) 63 woman owned brands.

🛍️ 800+ orders were packed in ♻️, bleach free bags, tissue and cotton. 
📦 We sent out ecom orders in ♻️ poly mailers & boxes made in the USA, taped w/ compostable stickers & tape….w/ recycled paper invoices & cards.

👗 We expanded our 2nd hand selection

🚮 We separated & took out our recyclables

💡 We changed out our lights for LED

🪵 We sourced fixtures locally, naturally & 2nd hand

It’s a joy to support a beautiful supply line. We don’t claim perfection, but are content to know our efforts are growing!

If you shopped with us in 2022, you too contributed to this impact, and we’re so grateful for you! 🙏

📸 @nadialeonphotography

$40 per child, All materials included (but do feel free to bring any photos they have handy & may want to include).

Use the QR code or 🔗 in stories & bio.

We took a minute to tally figures from 2023. I’m beyond grateful, because here’s what we found: 👇🏼

We carried
🌟 95 brands with verified ethical labor practices
🌟 42 brands that utilize verified sustainable materials
🌟 43 brands with local USA made manufacturing 
🌟 75 woman owned brands.

🛍️ 1100+ orders were packed in ♻️, bleach free bags, tissue, & compostable stickers
📦 We sent out ecom orders in ♻️ poly mailers & boxes made in the USA, taped w/ compostable tape….w/ recycled paper invoices & cards.

👗 We continued w/ our 2nd hand selection

🚮 We separated & took out our recyclables

💡 We used all LED lights

🪵 We sourced fixtures locally, naturally & 2nd hand

🫶 We grew in terms of community, donating & contributing to 10+ charities & local organizations 

It’s a joy to support a beautiful supply line. It’s a joy to know ALL OF YOU THROUGH THIS WORK. I don’t claim perfection, but am content to know our efforts are growing.

If you shopped with us in 2023, you too contributed to this impact, and we’re so grateful for you! 🙏
